Chairman informed that #Reliance is progressing well to deploy committed capital of Rs 75,000 crore to build New Energy manufacturing ecosystem. This will enable us to accelerate giga-scale production for round-the-clock power and for large-scale Green Hydrogen production. (29/n)

#Reliance targeted cost of electrolysers, and in turn, Green Hydrogen will set up a fully-integrated, automated, giga-scale electrolyser manufacturing facility. This will enable us to establish large-scale Green Hydrogen production at Jamnagar (28/n).

#Reliance  will install at least 100 GW of renewable energy generation by 2030. Its concurrent priority is to set up our Battery giga factory by 2026. It will manufacture battery chemicals, cells and packs, leading all the way up to containerised energy storage solutions. (27/n)

#Jio AirFibre, the much-awaited wireless home broadband service from #Reliance Jio, will be launched on Ganesh Chaturthi, which falls on September 19, 2023. The announcement was made by Reliance Industries chairman #MukeshAmbani at the company's 46th annual general meeting (AGM) on August 28, 2023. #RelianceAGM2023   ➖Jio AirFibre is a 5G-enabled service that promises to deliver ultra-fast internet speeds of up to 1Gbps. It will be available in all major cities across #India initially, and will be rolled out to other cities in the coming months.  ➖The service will be offered on a subscription basis, with plans starting at Rs. 699 per month. Jio is also offering a free trial of the service for 30 days.  ➖Jio AirFibre is expected to be a major disrupter in the Indian broadband market. It will compete with existing wired broadband services, as well as with the upcoming #5G mobile services.  ➖Jio has already made a significant investment in 5G, and it is expected to be one of the first companies to launch 5G services in India. Jio AirFibre will be a key part of the company's 5G strategy.  ➖With Jio #AirFibre, Reliance Jio is looking to make high-speed internet accessible to more people in India. The service is expected to be a game-changer for the Indian broadband market
